Yes Yes Yes. And a good tip is ... we went at 3pm. No lines! Shorter menu but everything we wanted. Best biscuit ever. Best Fried chicken. A little kicker of spice. Yum!

Overall: I would try this place one more time. Beignet: Decent, but I wouldn't order them again. French Toast: Pretty decent flavor. Chicken & Fries: Lack seasoning. Shrimp and Grits: Pretty good flavor, but too much cheese and not enough grit.

Finally came to Brenda's for brunch and it was everything that I expected (including the hour long wait). But so worth the wait. My dad and I ordered the beignet sampler platter since we couldn't make up our minds about which one to get and it was everything. There was one plain, one chocolate, one apple, & one crawfish. I don't eat crawfish but my dad said it was unreal. Even the plain was amazing (with their strawberry jam). My favorite was probably the apple though. We then split the veggie omelette and one half order of their special, Pumpkin Pancakes. The omelette was massive and perfect to share, and even came with cheesy grits (which i've actually never had before) and a biscuit. The cheesy grits were really really good. Who knew i liked grits? Our server was great - very attentive, helpful, and patient (we are very indecisive). Brenda's is also surprisingly affordable. Not very common here in SF. I was pleasantly surprised.

Don't forget to look up on the wall for another chalk board to see what's daily special besides looking on the menu. Atmosphere Great Music Awesome parking is a problem just be careful where you park at but hey this is San Francisco~

Disclaimer: The food deserves 5 stars for sure!!!! This review is strictly for our service. Was super excited to come here after seeing 9000+ reviews for this place!! I'm not super familiar with French food, so I was excited to try anything and everything. We were seated almost right away (made it before the huge dinner rush, so that was a plus!). For food, we ordered the crawfish beignets which were SO delicious. I got the chicken etouffee, which honestly was just rice and chicken with gravy, and nothing super special. The sweet potatoes dumplings were a pleasant surprise! I only tried a few bites, and it was quite sweet and interesting - definitely a different palette of flavors than I'm used to. The highlight though were the sweet beignets for dessert - YUM!! I would definitely come back for the beignets and beignets only haha :)

I enjoyed my brunch experience here, but it wasn't as amazing as the other reviews made it out to be. Perhaps my expectations were too high. The biggest disappointment for me was the Crawfish Beignets. The crawfish filling tasted great, but the beignets themselves were not well executed. They had an unbalanced batter to filling proportion and they were not very pillowy or soft as I like my beignets to be :( Definitely missed the mark for me. However, the Shrimp & Grits were delicious and highly recommended!! I loved that it was served with a tomato salsa on top, which gave it a bit of acidity for an otherwise very cheesey dish. Shrimp was also really fresh. I definitely want to give Brenda's another shot and next time will try the Hanger Fry and a po boy! Service was good here as well, the servers are very attentive and fast.

I visited Brenda's on a Saturday afternoon. There was a line formed and we were instructed to write our name on a chalkboard and the wait would be about 45 minutes (for 2). While in line we noticed it just kept growing, and more people would line up no matter how long it got.. this is when I knew it was worth the wait! Lol. We waited close to an hour and were then seated by the very adorably dressed hostess (who complimented my curly hair, thanks girl ! ) my husband and I shared a cup of gumbo which was super flavorful and delicious, we then each ordered the fried chicken Benedict. My husband loves eggs Benedict but I'd never tried it.. it was perfection! I really enjoyed it along with the hash. The only small thing I was disappointed about was I assumed we could choose between breakfast/brunch, or lunch based on the times stated available on the menu display outside. Only the brunch menu was available so I couldn't try the hush puppies which I was really looking forward to but it wasn't a big deal, just gives us another reason to go back. Everyone was really nice and the food very enjoyable, I definitely recommend Brenda's.

I came here with the boyfrannn a few weekends ago for brunch and the wait was SOOOoooo LONG. It was about 45 minutes!!!! Luckily, we found street parking literally less than a block away, BUT unfortunately, its the city and the parking meter aint cheappp. I think its like $3-$4 an hour. AND i was almost out of coins. We were really hungry, so we put our name down on the chalkboard and went into Libby Jane (sister store of Brendas that is next door) for a little gumbo while we waited. We also looked over the menu that was placed outside of the restaurant. It had its Breakfast, Lunch, Dinner, and Brunch menu. Unfortunately, what we found out when we got seated, they ONLY serve brunch on weekends, no lunch options. This means there is limited amount of food options you can get. This would be okay for others, but my boyfriend is allergic to eggs, so that limits him to only about 2-3 items on the menu. sigh ): Anyways, we ordered the: -Shrimp and Grits: MUST ORDER!!!! i have always thought grits sounded weird tasting, so i never order them. But this is SO GOOD. It comes in a slightly deep plate, oozing with cheese and spicy tomato saucy goodness! The shrimp is plentiful, juicy, and absorbed the spices that it was cooked in. -Croque Monsieur: one of the only other things that had no egg in it. Basically like a very sophisticated ham sandwich. The gruyere cheese was amazing though, as well as the creamy sauce they had in between the slices of bread. The fries had a nice salty taste. They also had a palate cleanser, which were small picked watermelon rind slices. Overall, had a great time here. This is a super cute restaurant, good for dates! It has a nice brunchy or slightly romantic vintage feel to it. Our waitress was kind and attentive and answered any questions we had about ingredients and food. I am definitely coming here again!!! this time ordering shit with eggs in it (we saw hella people ordering benedicts and beignets WHICH LOOKED SO GOOD), or coming in during lunch or dinner to try their other menu options.

Crawfish beignets + mimosas are a must for brunch here! The shrimp and grits were a bit too greasy for my preference but still super flavorful.

I cannot stop dreaming about this place! I am not a breakfast/brunch person, scrambled eggs or Benedict's don't really excite me anymore but Brenda's has restored my love for breakfast/brunch. There are no words to describe how darn delicious the crawfish beignets are. So soft on the inside and the crawfish filling was so amazing with the perfect mix of spices. Highly highly highly recommend that! We also tried shrimp and grits and the fried chicken Benedict. The shrimp and grits was also very good. The shrimp was fresh and flavorful but the best part was the tomato sauce that laid on top of the grits, giving each spoonful of grits so much good flavor. We couldn't stop eating even though we were full. The fried chicken Benedict is definitely more of a safe bet for those who aren't too in love with seafood. The chicken is fried to a perfect crisp and flavored to perfection as well. Definitely worth the wait if you're visiting San Francisco!
